**Steps to Reproduce**:
```C#
using System;

class Program
{
    public static void Main() { }

    public static void Throw(int index)
    {
        string name = "";
        switch (index)
        {
            case 0: name = "0"; break;
            case 1: name = "1"; break;
        }
        throw new Exception(name);
    }
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:
Either doesn't offer to refactor, or refactors to:
```C#
public static void Throw(int index)
{
    string name = index switch
    {
        0 => "0",
        1 => "1",
        _ => "",
    };
    throw new Exception(name);
}
```

